- Version / Branch: [e.g. v1.2.3 or main@abc1234]
- Runtime (if applicable): [e.g. Node 20, Python 3.12]

## Additional Context

Any other context relevant to this bug.
BUGREPORT
)

  upsert_file "$repo" \
    ".github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug_report.md" \
    "chore: apply tech-github-repo-standards bug report template" \
    "$(echo "$bug_report" | base64 -w 0)"

  # ── Feature request issue template ────────────────────────────────────────
  feature_request=$(cat <<'FEATUREREQUEST'
---
name: Feature Request
about: Suggest a new capability or improvement
labels: enhancement
assignees: ''
---

## Problem Statement

What problem are you trying to solve?

## Proposed Solution

Describe the feature and how it would work.

## Alternatives Considered

What other approaches did you consider?

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Criterion 1
- [ ] Criterion 2
- [ ] Criterion 3

## Additional Context

Mockups, related issues, prior art, or other supporting context.
FEATUREREQUEST
)

  upsert_file "$repo" \
    ".github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature_request.md" \
    "chore: apply tech-github-repo-standards feature request template" \
    "$(echo "$feature_request" | base64 -w 0)"

  # ── PR template ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # regulated profile adds a security checklist block
  if [[ "$PROFILE" == "regulated" ]]; then
    security_checklist="
- [ ] Security impact assessed — no new data exposure or privilege escalation introduced
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials, secrets, or PII introduced
- [ ] Complies with NYDFS 23 NYCRR 500 requirements (if in scope)
- [ ] Code scanning results reviewed; all alerts resolved or documented"
  else
    security_checklist=""
  fi

  pr_template=$(printf '%s\n' \
"## Summary

Brief description of what this PR does and why.

Closes #<!-- issue number, or delete if not applicable -->

## Type of Change

- [ ] Bug fix
- [ ] New feature
- [ ] Breaking change
- [ ] Documentation update
- [ ] Refactor (no functional changes)
- [ ] CI/CD or infrastructure change

## Changes Made

-
-
-

## Testing

- [ ] New tests added covering the changed behavior
- [ ] All existing tests pass locally
- [ ] Manually tested (steps below)

**Manual test steps:**

1.
2.

## Checklist

- [ ] Follows CONTRIBUTING.md conventions
- [ ] Self-reviewed
- [ ] Documentation updated where needed
- [ ] No new warnings or linting errors$security_checklist

## Screenshots (if applicable)

<!-- Before/after for UI changes; compliance evidence for regulated profile -->")

  upsert_file "$repo" \
    ".github/pull_request_template.md" \
    "chore: apply tech-github-repo-standards PR template ($PROFILE)" \
    "$(echo "$pr_template" | base64 -w 0)"

  # ── CodeQL workflow ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Applied: all profiles — committed file artifact
  # regulated profile adds SARIF artifact upload for audit evidence (90-day retention)
  # Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/code-security/code-scanning
  if [[ "$PROFILE" == "regulated" ]]; then
    evidence_step="
      # Upload SARIF as compliance evidence (regulated profile — 90-day retention)
      - name: Upload SARIF as compliance evidence
        if: always()
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: codeql-sarif-\${{ github.run_id }}
          path: /home/runner/work/_temp/codeql_databases/
          retention-days: 90"
  else
    evidence_step=""
  fi

  codeql_workflow=$(printf '%s\n' \
"# CodeQL Analysis — applied by tech-github-repo-standards (profile: $PROFILE)
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/code-security/code-scanning

name: CodeQL Analysis

on:
  push:
    branches: [main, develop]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]
  schedule:
    - cron: '0 2 * * 0'   # Weekly full scan: Sunday 02:00 UTC

permissions:
  contents: read
  security-events: write
  actions: read

jobs:
  analyze:
    name: Analyze (\${{ matrix.language }})
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    strategy:
      fail-fast: false
      matrix:
        # Adjust to the languages in this repo.
        # Supported: c-cpp, csharp, go, java-kotlin, javascript-typescript,
        #            python, ruby, swift
        language: [javascript-typescript]

    steps:
      - name: Checkout repository
        uses: actions/checkout@v6

      - name: Initialize CodeQL
        uses: github/codeql-action/init@v4
        with:
          languages: \${{ matrix.language }}
          # queries: security-and-quality   # uncomment for extended query suite

      - name: Autobuild
        uses: github/codeql-action/autobuild@v4

      - name: Perform CodeQL Analysis
        uses: github/codeql-action/analyze@v4
        with:
          category: \"/language:\${{ matrix.language }}\"
$evidence_step")

  upsert_file "$repo" \
    ".github/workflows/codeql.yml" \
    "ci: apply tech-github-repo-standards CodeQL workflow ($PROFILE)" \
    "$(echo "$codeql_workflow" | base64 -w 0)"

  # ── Dependabot version-updates config ──────────────────────────────────────
  # Enables scheduled dependency PRs alongside the security alerts/auto-fixes
  # that were enabled via the API. Detects common ecosystems; users should
  # remove unused entries or add ones for their stack.
  # Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/code-security/dependabot/dependabot-version-updates
  dependabot_yml=$(cat <<'DEPENDABOT'
# Dependabot version updates — applied by tech-github-repo-standards
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/code-security/dependabot/dependabot-version-updates/configuration-options-for-the-dependabot.yml-file
#
# Add or remove ecosystems below to match this repo. Common values:
#   npm, pip, gomod, maven, gradle, bundler, cargo, composer, nuget, docker
#
# `github-actions` is enabled below for every repo — workflows benefit from
# version pinning regardless of language.

version: 2
updates:
  - package-ecosystem: "github-actions"
    directory: "/"
    schedule:
      interval: "weekly"
    open-pull-requests-limit: 5
    labels:
      - "dependencies"
      - "ci"
    groups:
      # Batch all GitHub Actions bumps into a single weekly PR instead of
      # one PR per action. Avoids PR sprawl on fresh hardening runs where
      # several action versions are behind upstream.
      github-actions:
        patterns:
          - "*"

  # Uncomment and adjust for your primary language ecosystem:
  # - package-ecosystem: "npm"
  #   directory: "/"
  #   schedule:
  #     interval: "weekly"
  #   open-pull-requests-limit: 10
  #   groups:
  #     minor-and-patch:
  #       update-types: ["minor", "patch"]
  #   labels:
  #     - "dependencies"
DEPENDABOT
)

  upsert_file "$repo" \
    ".github/dependabot.yml" \
    "chore: apply tech-github-repo-standards Dependabot config" \
    "$(echo "$dependabot_yml" | base64 -w 0)"
}

# ── Main ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
main() {
  echo "════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════"
  echo " GitHub Repository Standards"
  echo " Context : $CONTEXT"
  echo " Profile : $PROFILE"
  echo " Org     : $ORG"
  [[ "$DRY_RUN" == "true" ]] && echo " Mode    : DRY RUN — no changes will be made"
  echo "════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════"
  echo ""

  # Verify gh CLI is installed and authenticated
  if ! gh auth status >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    echo "ERROR: gh CLI is not authenticated. Run: gh auth login"
    exit 1
  fi

  # Resolve repos (expand glob patterns)
  local all_repos=()
  for r in "${REPOS[@]}"; do
    while IFS= read -r resolved; do
      [[ -n "$resolved" ]] && all_repos+=("$resolved")
    done < <(resolve_repos "$r")
  done

  if [[ ${#all_repos[@]} -eq 0 ]]; then
    echo "ERROR: No repos found matching: ${REPOS[*]}"
    echo "       Check REPOS and verify org access: gh repo list $ORG"
    exit 1
  fi

  echo "Repos to configure (${#all_repos[@]}):"
  printf '  %s/%s\n' "$ORG" "${all_repos[@]}"
  echo ""

  for repo in "${all_repos[@]}"; do
    echo "────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────"
    echo " Configuring: $ORG/$repo"
    echo "────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────"

    apply_repo_settings "$repo"
    echo ""

    for branch in "${PROTECTED_BRANCHES[@]}"; do
      if gh api "/repos/$ORG/$repo/branches/$branch" >/dev/null 2>&1; then
        apply_branch_protection "$repo" "$branch"
      else
        echo "▸ Branch '$branch' not found — skipping protection"
        echo "  Create the branch first, then re-run this script."
        (( SETTINGS_SKIPPED++ )) || true
      fi
      echo ""
    done

    apply_security_settings "$repo"
    echo ""

    apply_actions_settings "$repo"
    echo ""

    apply_access "$repo"
    echo ""

    commit_artifacts "$repo"
    echo ""
  done

  # ── Summary ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  echo "════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════"
  echo " Summary"
  echo "════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════"
  printf " Context applied     : %s\n" "$CONTEXT"
  printf " Profile applied     : %s\n" "$PROFILE"
  printf " Repos configured    : %s\n" "${#all_repos[@]}"
  printf " Settings succeeded  : %s\n" "$SETTINGS_SUCCEEDED"
  printf " Settings skipped    : %s\n" "$SETTINGS_SKIPPED"
  printf " Settings failed     : %s\n" "$SETTINGS_FAILED"
  printf " Artifacts committed : %s\n" "$ARTIFACTS_COMMITTED"
  echo ""

  if [[ ${#MANUAL_STEPS[@]} -gt 0 ]]; then
    echo " Manual steps required:"
    for step in "${MANUAL_STEPS[@]}"; do
      echo "   • $step"
    done
    echo ""
  fi

  if [[ "$PROFILE" == "regulated" ]]; then
    echo " Regulated profile compliance checklist:"
    echo "   □ Confirm NYDFS scope with legal/compliance"
    echo "   □ Verify GitHub Advanced Security is licensed and enabled org-wide"
    echo "   □ Enable org-level 2FA enforcement (org Settings → Authentication security)"
    echo "   □ Confirm audit log streaming is configured for the org"
    echo "   □ Archive this script and generated artifacts as configuration evidence"
    echo "   □ Schedule quarterly review of branch protection and access settings"
    echo ""
  fi

  if [[ "$SETTINGS_FAILED" -gt 0 ]]; then
    echo " ✗ $SETTINGS_FAILED setting(s) failed. Review errors above before proceeding."
    exit 1
  else
    echo " ✓ All settings applied successfully."
  fi
}

main "$@"
